<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,469,367,391]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" reason="1">Biological observations.</emphasis>
Female can mate twice. Female lays batches of 60– 
<specimenCount box="[1024,1118,367,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" type="egg">150 eggs</specimenCount>
(up to 
<specimenCount box="[1194,1289,367,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" type="egg">664 eggs</specimenCount>
per female in total). Cannibalism was recorded for 6th instar larvae, which sometimes also consume pupae.
</paragraph>
